                <h1>Understanding Background Check Disputes</h1>
                <p>Disputing a background check means you challenge the accuracy of the information reported about you. This process can arise from discrepancies related to employment history, criminal records, or personal details. Successfully disputing can lead to corrections, ensuring the check reflects your true background for job applications or credit checks.</p>
